## Reasoning
To address the issue described, we need to consider the differences in how Quarkus handles producers compared to Java EE. In Quarkus, we can skip the `@Produces` annotation if the producer method is annotated with a scope annotation, a stereotype, or a qualifier.

However, in this case, the suggestion is to replace the field with a `@Named` getter method. This is because Quarkus uses CDI (Context and Dependency Injection) under the hood, and `@Named` is a CDI annotation that allows us to expose a bean as a named bean.

We will replace the `log` field with a getter method annotated with `@Named` and `@ApplicationScoped`. The `@ApplicationScoped` annotation is used to define the scope of the bean, which in this case is the application scope.

We will also remove the `@Produces` annotation from the `produceLog` method, as it is no longer needed.

## Updated java File
```java
package com.redhat.coolstore.utils;

import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;
import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Named;
import jakarta.enterprise.inject.spi.InjectionPoint;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

/**
 * This class is a helper class that provides a logger producer.
 */
public class Producers {

    @Named
    @ApplicationScoped
    public Logger getLogger() {
        return Logger.getLogger(Producers.class.getName());
    }

    public Logger produceLog(InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {
        return Logger.getLogger(injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass().getName());
    }

}
```

## Additional Information
Note that we have added the `@ApplicationScoped` annotation to the `getLogger` method. This is because in Quarkus, beans are not scoped by default, and we need to explicitly define the scope.

Also, we have removed the `log` field, as it is no longer needed. The `getLogger` method will now provide the logger instance.

In the `pom.xml` file, we need to make sure that the Quarkus CDI extension is included. This can be done by adding the following dependency:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>
    <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>
</dependency>
```
This dependency includes the Quarkus implementation of CDI, which is required for the `@Named` and `@ApplicationScoped` annotations to work.
